Whatever I am I am and I'm Love - I can't help it. I really can't help it. I'm Compassion. One day I did feel very disgusted, really. Once I did feel very disgusted with people the way they were and I was just saying that, "Forget it!" And then suddenly I saw My photograph and I saw My eyes, then I said, "Nirmala, you are Compassion, you're Compassion, you can't help it. You just can't help it. I have to work it out." I know it means, it means sometimes too much, too much, but I have to work it out.

